tion coefficients. For a\nMercury lander this rises to around 1% for a 1-month mission and 10 % for a\n4-year mission. By means of Monte Carlo simulation, we find that using an a\npriori time ephemeris of representative accuracy will result in estimation\nerrors that are orders of magnitude above the formal error when processing\nhighly accurate laser time transfer data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Dec 2015 16:21:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
