 column densities for absorption hosted by red galaxies with\n$D/R_{\\rm vir}$. Thus, a lack of outflows in red galaxies causes the CGM to\nbecome more quiescent over time, with lower velocity dispersions and larger\ncolumn densities towards lower $z_{\\rm gal}$. The quenching of star formation\nappears to affect the CGM out to $D/R_{\\rm vir}=0.75$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Dec 2015 06:24:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2016 01:51:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-09"}
